 up, due to the fact that each script follows different paths. Particular attention is also devoted to the use of Greek majuscules in the writing of ancient Christian books. A modern and critical awareness of palaeographic method may help to place the individual witnesses in the context of the main graphic trends, in the social and cultural environments in which they developed, and in a more accurate chronological framework.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aMajuscule scripts.  adating of manuscripts.  apalaeography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2019z978311071956708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE DG 2019 Englishz97831106168590 cEPUBz97831105755900 cprintz978311057540840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110575446zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110575446zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110575446.jpg  a978-3-11-061685-9 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE DG 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-071956-7 DG Plus eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA